WEBVTT

00:02.160 --> 00:03.446
NARRATOR:
Previously on Arrow:

00:03.640 --> 00:07.611
But there are some things
that must never be spoken of.

00:07.800 --> 00:11.282
How could you not tell me
Malcolm Merlyn was my father?

00:11.480 --> 00:13.084
Sara, you're not a killer.

00:13.320 --> 00:14.731
I am what I need to be.

00:14.920 --> 00:16.046
Roy, you're dangerous.

00:16.280 --> 00:17.441
[GRUNTING AND SHOUTING]

00:18.160 --> 00:19.207
Some people are broken.

00:19.400 --> 00:21.767
I'm not letting what happened to Slade
happen to Roy.

00:22.000 --> 00:23.240
Is that what I think it is?

00:23.440 --> 00:27.001
Mirakuru. We're gonna
use it to make a cure.

00:30.680 --> 00:32.250
No change?

00:32.439 --> 00:36.047
Nope. So much blood mixed in
with so much Mirakuru.

00:36.240 --> 00:38.607
I don't know if it's good or bad.

00:38.960 --> 00:42.521
- We could really use that cure.
- I talked to Caitlin this morning.

00:42.720 --> 00:43.881
We're working on it.

00:44.080 --> 00:46.606
- No mention on Isabel Rochev's death?
- Not a thing.

00:46.800 --> 00:50.043
I wasn't expecting a glowing obituary,
but she's a Fortune 500 CEO...

00:50.240 --> 00:54.609
that's been missing for a week now.
You'd think she'd have some column inches.

00:55.960 --> 00:57.803
[THUD THEN FELICITY GASPS]

01:00.080 --> 01:03.880
Does the fact that him lying there,
freak me out, make me a bad person?

01:04.120 --> 01:07.408
I don't think there's a force on Earth
that could make you a bad person.

01:07.600 --> 01:10.046
But I am starving. Dinner?

01:10.240 --> 01:11.810
Yeah.

01:12.280 --> 01:15.489
Uh, no Big Belly Burger though.
It's giving me a big belly.

01:15.720 --> 01:18.883
- Sushi then.
- Sushi then.

01:23.520 --> 01:27.286
How can you be unconscious
and freak me out at the same...

01:29.840 --> 01:31.524
time?

01:33.080 --> 01:34.764
Roy?

01:37.840 --> 01:39.683
Oh, my God.

01:40.640 --> 01:42.688
You scared me.

01:44.560 --> 01:47.609
- Roy?
- I forgot my phone.

01:52.280 --> 01:53.520
[FELICITY SCREAMS]

01:55.200 --> 01:56.611
Roy, listen.

01:57.520 --> 02:00.046
- Dig.
- You Okay?

02:00.240 --> 02:01.730
Roy.

02:01.920 --> 02:03.604
Roy.

02:03.800 --> 02:05.006
What's going on?

02:05.200 --> 02:07.282
[DANCE MUSIC PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

02:16.000 --> 02:19.243
Move, move, move.

02:40.920 --> 02:43.400
You think Roy's okay?

02:44.880 --> 02:48.441
Please tell me that you're not thinking
about Roy right now.

02:48.680 --> 02:50.887
We were finally alone...

02:51.080 --> 02:52.491
in bed...

02:52.680 --> 02:54.728
in a very nice hotel room.

02:54.920 --> 02:57.730
A hotel room that you couldn't afford.

02:58.440 --> 03:00.329
I have something of a history
with the manager.

03:00.520 --> 03:03.524
Mm. I can only imagine.

03:05.840 --> 03:09.208
I think I trashed this specific room once.

03:09.400 --> 03:11.721
But favors run out.

03:12.400 --> 03:15.449
We should think about getting
a more permanent place.

03:19.880 --> 03:21.609
We?

03:22.120 --> 03:25.966
Well, you're probably getting tired
of staying with Laurel...

03:26.160 --> 03:29.960
and we can't sleep in the foundry
now that Roy's there, so...

03:30.160 --> 03:32.686
But I mean, "we"?

03:32.880 --> 03:35.167
Are you asking me to move in with you?

03:38.840 --> 03:40.490
[CELL PHONE BUZZING]

03:40.680 --> 03:44.287
- Hey, your phone's ringing.
- I know.

03:46.360 --> 03:47.725
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

03:47.920 --> 03:51.561
Okay, both our phones are ringing.
That's never good.

03:59.400 --> 04:02.085
- What happened?
- I don't know. One minute, he's comatose...

04:02.280 --> 04:04.567
the next, he's flipping over
computer equipment.

04:04.800 --> 04:06.928
He's a lot more out of control
than Slade was.

04:07.120 --> 04:09.930
He looked like Roy but he wasn't Roy.

04:10.120 --> 04:13.488
- Where do you think he's headed?
- I don't know, but we have to find him.

04:16.000 --> 04:20.483
Despite predictions, you've managed to pull
ahead of Sebastian Blood in recent polls.

04:20.680 --> 04:24.082
Yes. I think our message
is resonating with the voters.

04:24.320 --> 04:27.608
The people of Starling know
that I have a vision...

04:27.800 --> 04:30.963
and the experienced apparatus
to make that vision a reality.

04:31.200 --> 04:34.488
What is the main reason they should vote
for you over Alderman Blood?

04:34.680 --> 04:36.648
Well, um...

04:36.920 --> 04:39.890
Alderman Blood isn't a parent.

04:40.520 --> 04:45.481
And the soul of being a parent is making sure
that your children have a bright future...

04:45.720 --> 04:48.564
and I've been very lucky
to be able to do that for my own.

04:48.800 --> 04:50.848
THEA:
Yeah, mother of the year.

04:51.440 --> 04:53.647
Uh, we're in the middle of an interview.

04:53.840 --> 04:56.810
I'll keep it short.
You can't have your rally at Verdant.

04:57.320 --> 05:00.130
It's the only place I have
that hasn't been poisoned by you.

05:00.360 --> 05:02.328
Can you give me one moment, please?

05:02.520 --> 05:03.567
Turn it off.

05:03.760 --> 05:06.525
Thea, I know you're upset,
and you have every right to be...

05:06.720 --> 05:09.530
- but we need to talk somewhere else.
- I'm done talking.

05:09.720 --> 05:13.520
I just came by to tell you it'll be a cold
day in hell before you can use my club.

05:13.720 --> 05:17.691
- We can't just change the venue the day before.
- I'm sure you can figure something out.

05:17.920 --> 05:20.048
I mean, you have such
an experienced apparatus.

05:20.240 --> 05:21.765
You signed a contract.

05:22.680 --> 05:24.170
Huh.

05:25.160 --> 05:28.130
Just when I thought
you couldn't go any lower...

05:28.320 --> 05:31.210
you threaten your own daughter.

05:39.080 --> 05:40.844
Moira.

05:41.160 --> 05:42.924
What's going on?

05:44.160 --> 05:45.571
Sorry you had to witness that.

05:45.760 --> 05:48.889
After her abduction, I'd think the
two of you'd be closer than ever.

05:49.080 --> 05:51.367
It's a very complicated situation.

05:51.560 --> 05:53.369
Well, my advice?

05:53.560 --> 05:55.449
Simplify it.

05:55.760 --> 05:58.650
You have to be either a mother
or a candidate.

05:58.840 --> 06:01.127
You can't be both. Not right now.

06:01.320 --> 06:04.483
You cannot split your focus.

06:06.040 --> 06:08.361
You're absolutely right.

06:10.840 --> 06:13.002
You're cute when you're mopey.

06:14.120 --> 06:16.407
I'm not mopey.

06:17.880 --> 06:20.167
Mopey's your default, Ollie.

06:20.400 --> 06:23.404
It's part of your smoldering charm.

06:23.840 --> 06:26.764
- I do have smoldering charm.
- Ha, ha.

06:28.840 --> 06:31.764
But you're more-than-usual mopey.

06:32.360 --> 06:34.647
Is everything all right?

06:40.200 --> 06:42.043
It's fine.

06:45.360 --> 06:46.930
Ollie?

06:47.120 --> 06:52.251
Tommy had me out a little bit later
than maybe I should have been and...

06:52.720 --> 06:55.291
Heh. What, I'm wiped?

06:56.800 --> 06:58.040
Well, you want me to go?

06:58.240 --> 07:00.561
I promised Sara I'd help her
with her trigonometry.

07:00.760 --> 07:02.285
I don't know what that is.

07:02.680 --> 07:05.570
You are very cute.

07:09.240 --> 07:11.242
- Get some sleep.
- Mm-hm.

07:14.160 --> 07:15.730
Bye.

07:15.920 --> 07:17.570
Bye.

07:18.120 --> 07:21.010
- Good night, Mrs. Queen.
MOIRA: Good night.

07:26.360 --> 07:30.410
- You didn't go outwith Tommy last night.
- Ha, ha.

07:30.720 --> 07:35.886
Okay. Thank you for eavesdropping on
my entire conversation, Morn. That's nice.

07:36.080 --> 07:39.801
Sweetheart, something's bothering you.
Tell me what it is.

07:42.960 --> 07:45.167
Dad's gonna kill me.

07:45.400 --> 07:46.845
Your father loves you.

07:47.040 --> 07:49.008
- I love you.
- I screwed up.

07:51.440 --> 07:53.010
It's bad.

07:55.280 --> 07:56.520
What happened?

08:00.160 --> 08:02.640
I got a girl pregnant.

08:03.760 --> 08:06.081
Laurel's pregnant?

08:07.560 --> 08:09.289
No.

08:11.760 --> 08:13.091
Not Laurel.

08:22.040 --> 08:26.250
This is ridiculous. We can't just ride
around all night, hoping to lay eyes on him.

08:26.720 --> 08:27.767
Diggle.

08:27.960 --> 08:30.440
His place is clean.
I don't think he's been back here.

08:30.640 --> 08:33.450
A call just went out for an ambulance
at 14th and Hobart.

08:33.640 --> 08:37.087
There's four men seriously assaulted
by someone wearing a red hoodie.

08:48.960 --> 08:50.724
What happened?

08:50.960 --> 08:53.201
Guy jumped us. It came out of nowhere.

08:54.080 --> 08:56.287
Dude is roided out or something.

08:56.720 --> 08:58.688
Crazy-like.

09:00.960 --> 09:03.327
MAN: See you, Sin.
- Adios.

09:03.640 --> 09:05.722
Yo, Abercrombie.

09:05.920 --> 09:06.967
Hold up.

09:07.160 --> 09:08.844
Where you been, man?

09:09.040 --> 09:12.203
I went over your place, like, 20 times.
Thea said you skipped town.

09:15.920 --> 09:19.242
Holy crap. Have you been in a fight?

09:20.320 --> 09:21.367
Hey!

09:21.600 --> 09:23.648
MAN:
Hey, Sin. This guy bothering you?

09:23.840 --> 09:26.411
No, no, no. It's chill.
Seriously, just step off.

09:26.600 --> 09:30.491
- We gonna have a problem, guy?
- Seriously? Just leave him alone. He's fine.

09:30.680 --> 09:32.444
What, you got nothing smart to say?

09:32.640 --> 09:34.085
[SCREAMING]

09:53.360 --> 09:55.931
Felicity's running facial recognition
on traffic cameras.

09:56.120 --> 09:59.806
Which could take forever. We need to take
Roy down before he attacks more people.

10:00.000 --> 10:03.402
What part of "I want nothing to do
with you" are you not understanding?

10:03.600 --> 10:05.807
I came by to see Sara.

10:06.200 --> 10:08.601
And what about him? He's been stalking me.

10:08.800 --> 10:10.484
- He's protecting you.
THEA: From what?

10:10.680 --> 10:12.444
Slade Wilson is still at large.

10:12.640 --> 10:16.281
- He already tried hurting you once.
- He didn't hurt me. He told me the truth.

10:16.480 --> 10:19.768
Which I know you think is a bad thing,
but it's actually not.

10:19.960 --> 10:21.166
It is if it cost me you.

10:21.840 --> 10:23.365
Your lies did that.

10:24.440 --> 10:28.081
I'm gonna go up to the stockroom, and if
I get attacked by some shot glasses...

10:28.280 --> 10:29.520
I'll call 911.

10:33.640 --> 10:35.005
Thanks for taking care of her.

10:35.200 --> 10:38.044
Lucky for me, she's not as good
at disappearing as you are.

10:42.040 --> 10:44.088
I'll be right back.

10:44.680 --> 10:47.047
- Have you seen Thea?
- What happened to your eye?

10:47.240 --> 10:50.528
It's okay. I could cover it with makeup,
if I wore makeup.

10:50.720 --> 10:53.041
- It's fine.
- Who did this to you?

10:53.240 --> 10:55.004
SIN: It's a long story.
- I asked you who.

10:56.320 --> 10:57.890
Roy.

10:58.080 --> 10:59.809
But he's not right in the head.

11:00.000 --> 11:03.527
He got injected with something, a drug,
I don't know, but it made him strong.

11:03.760 --> 11:05.444
Like comic-book strong.

11:05.680 --> 11:09.048
- Look, I know it sounds nuts...
- No, it really doesn't.

11:09.240 --> 11:12.881
Sara, Roy's a friend.
He needs help, not a beatdown.

11:18.760 --> 11:21.047
I'll have to call you right back.

11:22.680 --> 11:24.409
You want me to stay, Mr. Blood?

11:24.600 --> 11:28.605
Uh, no, Clinton, thank you. We'll be fine.

11:31.600 --> 11:34.331
My new body man,
he's a little overprotective.

11:34.520 --> 11:37.126
- Please.
- No, thank you.

11:37.720 --> 11:40.769
I'd say this visit is unexpected
but I despise understatement.

11:40.960 --> 11:44.931
I'm dropping out of the race. I'm making
a concession speech at my rally tonight.

11:45.120 --> 11:47.327
You're ahead in the latest polls.

11:47.560 --> 11:50.609
Even the most skeptical pundits are saying
you could pull this out.

11:50.800 --> 11:53.451
I felt I owed you the courtesy
of informing you in person.

11:53.640 --> 11:57.884
I don't, however,
owe you an explanation as well.

11:58.080 --> 11:59.889
No, you don't.

12:00.520 --> 12:02.887
But I'd appreciate one.

12:04.880 --> 12:08.771
What you're doing, Moira,
as much as it benefits me...

12:08.960 --> 12:11.327
doesn't really make much sense.

12:16.160 --> 12:18.242
It's my daughter.

12:18.600 --> 12:21.285
At the moment, she needs me
more than Starling does.

12:22.520 --> 12:24.841
Well, you're doing the right thing.

12:26.440 --> 12:29.762
I am going to change this city, Moira.

12:30.320 --> 12:31.446
A new day is coming.

12:31.680 --> 12:33.250
A better day...

12:33.480 --> 12:35.528
for all of us.

12:37.320 --> 12:41.644
I know things seem bleak, sweetheart,
but we're gonna figure this out, I promise.

12:41.840 --> 12:44.081
Mom, it doesn't seem fair...

12:44.320 --> 12:46.084
to me.

12:49.360 --> 12:51.840
One mistake and it...

12:52.360 --> 12:55.091
It feels like my entire life is over.

12:55.360 --> 12:58.364
Your life is far from over.

13:00.960 --> 13:03.361
Are you sure it's yours?

13:05.560 --> 13:09.326
Where there is money, Oliver,
there are people looking to take advantage.

13:09.520 --> 13:12.603
She's not that type of person.
She's a good person, Mom. She's...

13:12.800 --> 13:14.689
All right.

13:15.880 --> 13:18.201
I don't know what to do. What do I do?

13:20.840 --> 13:22.046
Heh.

13:23.680 --> 13:25.170
We all make mistakes, Oliver.

13:25.400 --> 13:30.201
And I'd hope that one day you'd forgive me
for any that I might make, so...

13:31.480 --> 13:34.848
All right. Um, I'll be right back.

13:38.400 --> 13:41.210
FELICITY: Verdant, 14th and Hobart,
and the bar Sin spotted him at.

13:41.400 --> 13:43.687
- He looks to be moving east.
- What east?

13:43.920 --> 13:45.524
Queen mansion.

13:45.760 --> 13:47.808
If he still remembers where Thea lives...

13:48.000 --> 13:50.241
Well, you used to live,
but Roy doesn't know that.

13:50.440 --> 13:52.727
There might be something of Roy
still in there.

13:52.920 --> 13:54.763
Or it's a coincidence he's moving east.

13:55.640 --> 13:58.723
I know that Sin's involved,
but don't let that cloud your judgment.

13:58.920 --> 14:01.844
Well, don't let the fact
that this used to be Roy, cloud yours.

14:06.760 --> 14:08.728
- Sin.
SIN [OVER PHONE]: I found Roy.

14:08.920 --> 14:10.524
I thought I told you to go home.

14:10.720 --> 14:13.200
Yeah, that's where I am right now.

14:13.560 --> 14:15.562
And so is he.

14:24.040 --> 14:25.565
Roy.

14:37.960 --> 14:39.200
He's not here.

14:42.480 --> 14:43.845
[GROWLING]

14:46.520 --> 14:48.488
[GRUNTING AND SHOUTING]

15:03.160 --> 15:05.083
It's Oliver.

15:05.320 --> 15:07.163
It's me.

15:07.440 --> 15:09.363
What you're doing right now...

15:09.560 --> 15:11.528
it's because of the Mirakuru.

15:11.760 --> 15:15.242
You're a good person, Roy.
You have a conscience and a soul.

15:15.440 --> 15:19.889
I need you to use those and fight this.
You can do it.

15:20.080 --> 15:22.048
[GRUNTING AND SHOUTING]

15:26.200 --> 15:27.486
[SCREAMING]

15:35.200 --> 15:36.690
[TIRES SQUEALING AND SIRENS WAILING]

15:38.760 --> 15:40.250
Drop the arrow. Drop it.

15:44.400 --> 15:46.323
[OLIVER GRUNTS]

15:49.600 --> 15:51.284
[SCREAMING]

15:53.000 --> 15:54.161
No!

16:09.320 --> 16:12.483
A full moon tonight,
that really brings out the whack jobs.

16:12.680 --> 16:16.048
Good news is, it can't get any stranger.

16:16.280 --> 16:18.203
My friend needs your help.

16:18.400 --> 16:21.563
I was wrong. Gotta call you back.

16:22.600 --> 16:24.409
Some of this damage is chronic.

16:24.600 --> 16:26.921
The cost of jumping off rooftops, I guess.

16:27.120 --> 16:29.202
I need to get back on my feet.

16:29.400 --> 16:33.166
I can give you a brace, but you'll still be
in horrendous amounts of pain.

16:33.360 --> 16:35.567
Six months ago,
this cabinet would've been empty.

16:35.800 --> 16:38.849
The Chinese Triad was stopping
all of our med shipments...

16:39.040 --> 16:41.520
until someone stopped them.

16:41.960 --> 16:45.442
Ever since, I've been looking for a way
to thank you.

16:58.160 --> 17:02.529
If you're gonna have to follow me
everywhere, at least don't lurk, all right?

17:05.599 --> 17:07.250
DIGGLE:
I can't let you out of my sight...

17:09.119 --> 17:13.204
and you're sick of seeing me everywhere you
go. Lurking seemed like a good compromise.

17:13.400 --> 17:16.165
Yeah, well, it's not.

17:20.280 --> 17:23.204
Family's hard.
Sometimes they're the hardest in the world.

17:23.400 --> 17:25.880
Loving someone so much
and letting them love you back.

17:26.079 --> 17:28.731
You know, you're right.
You should go back to lurking.

17:28.920 --> 17:30.729
I spend a lot of time with your family.

17:30.920 --> 17:33.207
Think that gives you the right to weigh in,
wrong.

17:33.440 --> 17:36.364
Plus, Oliver will be out of money soon
and you'll be unemployed.

17:36.560 --> 17:40.565
Right. Then I guess I should get this in
under the wire.

17:40.760 --> 17:42.762
You know, your mother isn't perfect.

17:42.960 --> 17:44.803
Her judgment definitely isn't.

17:45.360 --> 17:48.489
There's one thing she's consistent about,
she loves you and Oliver.

17:48.680 --> 17:50.728
And that should buy her what, in your mind?

17:51.320 --> 17:53.641
Hell, I don't know, Thea.

17:54.360 --> 17:56.283
But she is your mother...

17:56.480 --> 17:58.562
that should buy her something.

17:59.160 --> 18:01.288
A second chance maybe?

18:02.400 --> 18:07.361
Perpetrator of an attack that left one police
officer seriously injured and the other dead.

18:07.600 --> 18:10.331
We have video shot by a bystander...

18:10.560 --> 18:14.201
but please be warned that the footage
maybe too graphic for some viewers.

18:16.920 --> 18:18.410
Oh, my God.

18:18.600 --> 18:20.682
- Thea?
- I have to go see a friend.

18:20.880 --> 18:23.247
If you have to follow, follow.

18:25.160 --> 18:26.650
These aren't gonna fix your knee.

18:26.840 --> 18:29.525
- They'll help it heal faster.
- And until then?

18:31.400 --> 18:35.405
- Where are we with facial recognition?
- Traffic cams can't get a clear shot.

18:35.600 --> 18:38.080
- Now I see why you wear that hood.
- Felicity.

18:39.240 --> 18:41.208
We need to find Roy before the police do.

18:41.400 --> 18:43.368
Because they'll kill him and we won't?

18:44.480 --> 18:47.882
- S.T.A.R. Labs is working on a cure.
- Which they may never come up with.

18:48.080 --> 18:51.527
Even if they do, how many people
are we gonna let Roy kill in the meantime?

18:51.720 --> 18:54.200
You wanted to kill Helena too.
You found another way.

18:54.440 --> 18:58.445
That was different and you know it. Roy
has the Mirakuru in him, just like Slade.

18:58.640 --> 19:01.291
If you had a clear shot at Slade right now,
you'd take it.

19:01.480 --> 19:02.811
Roy isn't Slade.

19:03.000 --> 19:04.240
Roy isn't Roy.

19:04.440 --> 19:07.649
He's not himself anymore.
He's too far gone.

19:08.160 --> 19:09.321
I don't believe that.

19:11.120 --> 19:13.600
Do you even hear yourself right now, Ollie?

19:13.800 --> 19:17.009
This is the exact conversation
that we had five years ago...

19:17.200 --> 19:19.441
except we were freezing on Lian Yu.

19:28.920 --> 19:31.161
OLIVER: What are you doing?
- What needs to be done.

19:31.360 --> 19:33.727
Mirakuru won't do anything
against a head shot.

19:33.920 --> 19:36.207
- Sara.
- Your mother's rally starts in half an hour.

19:36.440 --> 19:38.602
I'd start getting dressed, if I were you.

19:45.280 --> 19:46.566
[SIGHS]

19:52.440 --> 19:55.762
She reminds me so much of me
after I came home.

19:56.600 --> 19:58.807
When it just seemed...

19:59.280 --> 20:03.569
It seemed impossible to believe in
anything even resembling hope.

20:03.800 --> 20:04.847
But you did.

20:05.680 --> 20:07.364
You did.

20:08.080 --> 20:09.923
Eventually.

20:11.080 --> 20:12.320
Sara will too.

20:23.400 --> 20:26.722
THEA: Thanks for coming.
- It's chill. Who's that?

20:27.320 --> 20:29.800
Uh, my shadow.

20:30.040 --> 20:32.008
Uh, listen, something is going on with Roy.

20:32.200 --> 20:34.168
I know. I saw him. He's totally crazed.

20:34.360 --> 20:36.089
What's happening to him?

20:39.320 --> 20:41.846
Do you remember around Christmas
when he bailed on us?

20:42.480 --> 20:46.280
- Yeah?
- He got shot up with something, this drug...

20:46.480 --> 20:48.448
and it's been messing with his head.

20:48.680 --> 20:50.364
Did you tell my brother any of this?

20:51.360 --> 20:52.771
No. Why?

20:52.960 --> 20:55.281
He's had this bodyguard all over me.

20:55.520 --> 20:58.808
He must know about Roy,
think he's coming after me or something.

20:59.000 --> 21:00.206
What are you gonna do?

21:06.480 --> 21:08.323
TH EA:
Roy?

21:09.200 --> 21:10.804
Roy, it's me.

21:11.840 --> 21:13.251
It's Thea.

21:15.320 --> 21:18.051
I'm so glad I found you.

21:18.240 --> 21:20.846
I've been looking everywhere.

21:22.360 --> 21:24.761
This is all my fault.

21:24.960 --> 21:27.247
I did this to you.

21:27.440 --> 21:30.284
When you broke up with me,
it was a cry for help...

21:30.480 --> 21:32.642
and I didn't listen.

21:34.880 --> 21:37.531
I should be punished.

21:38.120 --> 21:40.646
I deserve to be punished.

21:40.840 --> 21:45.289
Someone hurts you, you hurt them worse.

21:45.560 --> 21:48.166
You hurt them permanently.

21:50.200 --> 21:52.328
You should just kill me.

21:52.520 --> 21:53.681
Kill me.

21:55.680 --> 21:57.682
Kill me.

22:01.080 --> 22:02.650
MARK:
Oliver, where have you been?

22:02.880 --> 22:05.884
- Haven't you gotten any of my calls?
- I've been busy. What's wrong?

22:06.080 --> 22:08.208
- It's your mother.
- She'll do fine.

22:08.400 --> 22:10.084
No, she won't.

22:10.280 --> 22:14.410
She's not using this event to rally
the troops. She's using it...

22:14.640 --> 22:16.961
to tell people she's dropping out
of the race.

22:24.920 --> 22:26.763
Oliver.

22:27.760 --> 22:29.250
What happened?

22:29.440 --> 22:33.081
It's a motorcycle accident. It was stupid.

22:33.280 --> 22:37.001
Yes, this would be the second accident
in as many weeks...

22:37.200 --> 22:40.443
- if my math is correct.
- Mark says you're dropping out of the race.

22:41.960 --> 22:44.850
The truth is I should have done it
weeks ago...

22:45.040 --> 22:46.280
after Thea was abducted.

22:46.480 --> 22:50.087
My complete focus needs to be
on repairing our relationship.

22:50.280 --> 22:54.410
What's happening with Thea now isn't because
you weren't spending enough time with her.

22:54.640 --> 22:59.202
Well, maybe not. But I have to do something,
and I'm not sure what else to do.

23:00.800 --> 23:04.168
Thea hates you right now
because of the things that you've done.

23:04.960 --> 23:07.008
Terrible things.

23:08.440 --> 23:12.001
So let her see you do something good...

23:12.480 --> 23:13.561
as mayor.

23:18.920 --> 23:22.163
Mom, I know a little something about...

23:23.680 --> 23:26.604
sacrificing the people closest to me...

23:26.840 --> 23:29.320
for the good of this city.

23:29.640 --> 23:31.051
It's what you need to do now.

23:33.960 --> 23:35.689
I know.

23:37.240 --> 23:39.083
Good.

23:39.560 --> 23:41.324
Oliver, I know.

23:44.480 --> 23:46.528
I know.

23:56.880 --> 24:00.407
I've known since last year, I suppose.

24:01.680 --> 24:06.208
The night of the Undertaking,
everything became so clear.

24:07.600 --> 24:10.490
It's pretty much the night I stop sleeping.

24:10.680 --> 24:13.684
- Before you say anything else...
- There's nothing else to say.

24:13.880 --> 24:15.530
Nothing I need to say.

24:19.720 --> 24:22.291
Except I could not be more proud.

24:27.200 --> 24:30.010
Can I have Raisa get you anything to drink?

24:30.200 --> 24:33.568
Or something to eat perhaps? Please.

24:34.920 --> 24:36.524
Where's Oliver?

24:36.720 --> 24:39.530
He's running an errand for me.

24:39.720 --> 24:42.929
I thought it would give
us a chance to talk.

24:47.720 --> 24:51.088
With all due respect, um, Mrs. Queen...

24:51.280 --> 24:53.726
what's happening,
it's between me and your son.

24:53.920 --> 24:55.410
Yes.

25:02.640 --> 25:03.687
What is that?

25:03.880 --> 25:07.089
Oh, I had one of our investigators
write up at dossier on you.

25:07.280 --> 25:11.729
I'm sorry, but it's a necessary precaution
against a fraudulent claim of paternity.

25:11.920 --> 25:13.410
Well, the baby is Oliver's.

25:13.600 --> 25:17.366
Oh. Of that, I have no doubt.
Our investigators were quite thorough.

25:17.560 --> 25:19.403
But you can imagine...

25:19.600 --> 25:25.289
how many people my family attracts
who are looking for handouts.

25:25.600 --> 25:27.204
Well, I'm not looking for money.

25:29.600 --> 25:30.647
Of course not.

25:33.000 --> 25:35.082
I told you I don't want money.

25:35.280 --> 25:39.410
And I'm telling you
that this is my first grandchild.

25:39.640 --> 25:44.089
And I wanna make certain
that he or she has a bright future.

25:44.600 --> 25:45.647
Please.

25:49.680 --> 25:51.887
This is a million dollars.

25:52.080 --> 25:55.084
I wanna make certain
that my son has a bright future as well.

25:56.120 --> 25:57.884
That money is yours...

25:58.080 --> 26:01.971
once you tell Oliver
that you've lost the baby.

26:02.320 --> 26:03.367
What?

26:03.560 --> 26:07.884
And another million when you return to
Central City never to speak to him again.

26:08.840 --> 26:12.686
Can I offer you some advice,
one mother to another?

26:12.920 --> 26:16.606
When it comes to your children,
there is no action that is inconceivable...

26:16.840 --> 26:19.127
there's no decision that is impossible.

26:19.520 --> 26:22.285
You do what you must
to provide the life that they need.

26:22.480 --> 26:26.451
And I think that $2
million is sufficient...

26:26.680 --> 26:29.365
to provide the life
that both our children need.

26:32.560 --> 26:34.528
Don't you?

26:35.960 --> 26:38.327
[CROWD CHEERING]

26:42.640 --> 26:45.962
When I was first approached
about entering this race...

26:46.200 --> 26:51.650
the prospect of winning seemed a
distant, nearly impossible feat.

26:51.880 --> 26:54.201
How could a city
that had suffered so much...

26:54.400 --> 26:58.166
place its faith in someone
so responsible for its suffering?

26:58.960 --> 27:01.440
But as the weeks progressed...

27:01.680 --> 27:05.002
good people such as you
raised your voices in support...

27:05.200 --> 27:08.249
and I began to think
that I could make a difference.

27:08.480 --> 27:11.370
I could help save this city.

27:16.040 --> 27:17.769
But...

27:18.800 --> 27:22.441
recent events have
changed things, and...

27:35.960 --> 27:38.691
And now I know I can make a difference.

27:38.920 --> 27:40.410
[CROWD CHEERING]

27:43.400 --> 27:48.122
Should the honor become mine,
I promise with every breath I take...

27:48.320 --> 27:50.049
to do what is necessary.

27:50.240 --> 27:54.290
To sacrifice what is necessary
for the good of this city.

27:54.520 --> 27:57.046
Starling City is my home,
you are my family...

27:57.240 --> 28:01.529
and there is nothing more
important to me than family.

28:02.280 --> 28:04.442
Thank you. Thank you, all.

28:04.640 --> 28:05.926
[CROWD CHEERING]

28:07.760 --> 28:08.807
Great speech, Moira.

28:09.040 --> 28:12.089
- A little too off-book for my liking...
- Thank you.

28:12.280 --> 28:14.806
- but we'll work on that.
- I thought it was perfect.

28:15.040 --> 28:16.610
Uh, um...

28:17.040 --> 28:18.644
Hi.

28:19.000 --> 28:22.129
I just wanted to come up here
and say a few words.

28:22.800 --> 28:26.122
I am so proud to have my mom here tonight.

28:26.320 --> 28:29.085
At my club, Verdant, in the Glades.

28:29.280 --> 28:30.327
What is she doing?

28:30.560 --> 28:33.325
She knows this is being televised.

28:33.680 --> 28:37.480
She's sending a message to Roy.
Trying to draw him out.

28:37.960 --> 28:42.045
Vote Queen. Tell your friends. Thanks.

28:42.800 --> 28:46.043
- Thea...
- That was not for you.

28:51.520 --> 28:53.010
[GROANS]

28:53.480 --> 28:56.802
Oh, my God, you're heavy.
Is this really all muscle?

28:57.040 --> 28:59.486
- How many of those vitaminerals do we have?
- About 20.

28:59.680 --> 29:02.684
- I need all of them.
- Okay. Are you sure that's a good idea?

29:02.920 --> 29:05.127
Can you even get into those pants
with that knee?

29:05.320 --> 29:07.129
Lidocaine, now.

29:07.320 --> 29:08.924
FELICITY:
Okay.

29:13.080 --> 29:16.527
- Let's see, the bottle says the
proper dose... - ls all of it.

29:16.720 --> 29:19.200
- I don't think that's a good...
- Mm.

29:24.320 --> 29:25.401
Oh.

29:28.560 --> 29:31.643
Terrific speech. How did we not think
of running you years ago?

29:31.840 --> 29:33.126
Well, thank you.

29:35.120 --> 29:38.408
- Uh, can you give me a moment?
- Of course.

29:39.200 --> 29:40.440
Oh, hello.

29:40.640 --> 29:42.369
[GUNFIRE]

29:46.000 --> 29:48.480
- We need to go now.
THEA: I can't leave without my daughter.

29:48.720 --> 29:51.849
I'll see to the safety of your daughter.
Go. Thea, we have to go now.

29:52.040 --> 29:54.611
No, it's Roy. I'm not leaving him.
He came here for me.

30:04.280 --> 30:05.691
Roy.

30:05.880 --> 30:08.884
Roy, listen to me. Listen to my voice.

30:09.080 --> 30:10.684
I don't know what's going on...

30:10.880 --> 30:15.363
but I have to believe the man I fell in
love with is still inside there, somewhere.

30:15.560 --> 30:18.848
You have to fight.
You're strong, you can fight this.

30:19.080 --> 30:20.445
Fight this.

30:20.640 --> 30:22.085
[GASPING]

30:27.120 --> 30:28.884
SARA:
Roy.

30:30.680 --> 30:32.409
Put her down.

30:36.560 --> 30:38.847
No. Please, don't.

30:39.040 --> 30:41.611
- He can't control it.
- That's why I don't have a choice.

30:41.800 --> 30:43.131
SIN:
Roy.

30:43.360 --> 30:45.010
- Get out of the way.
- Don't do this.

30:52.280 --> 30:53.441
Kill me.

30:54.080 --> 30:56.560
Please, kill me.

30:57.280 --> 30:58.850
THEA:
Please, don't do it.

31:08.560 --> 31:10.801
No one dies tonight.

31:11.200 --> 31:13.009
You've got the police.

31:13.200 --> 31:14.440
Go outside.

31:14.680 --> 31:17.809
We'll get Roy the help he needs.
I promise. Go.

31:23.720 --> 31:25.051
Tibetan pit-viper venom.

31:25.240 --> 31:27.561
Constant dose of that
can't be good for you, right?

31:27.760 --> 31:31.651
- It'll keep him sedated like it did Slade.
- Until when? What happens when we run out?

31:31.840 --> 31:34.684
Not like you can buy this
over the counter, unless you're in Tibet.

31:34.880 --> 31:37.360
Then maybe.

31:37.560 --> 31:39.289
We'll take care of him.

31:45.080 --> 31:47.811
I'm not ready to give up on Roy.

31:50.480 --> 31:53.404
Anyone else crave dim sum after fisticuffs?

31:54.400 --> 31:57.483
No? Okay, dumplings for one then.

32:01.160 --> 32:03.242
I Would've killed him.

32:04.680 --> 32:06.921
I was ready to.

32:07.680 --> 32:10.126
He'd be dead right now
if you hadn't have stopped me.

32:10.360 --> 32:11.805
But he's not.

32:12.840 --> 32:14.888
That's all that matters.

32:15.080 --> 32:17.128
SARA:
That's not true.

32:17.800 --> 32:20.610
I wanted to kill Roy...

32:21.280 --> 32:23.726
because that's what I do.

32:23.960 --> 32:26.122
That's who I am.

32:26.520 --> 32:29.364
I spent six years in the darkness...

32:29.720 --> 32:32.485
and I looked into the
eyes of the devil...

32:32.720 --> 32:35.291
and I gave him my soul.

32:37.040 --> 32:38.530
Let me help you get it back.

32:39.080 --> 32:41.287
No, you deserve someone better.

32:42.080 --> 32:45.926
Someone who can harness that light
that's still inside of you.

32:46.880 --> 32:49.326
But I'm not that person.

32:49.920 --> 32:52.730
- And I never will be.
- Sara.

32:54.760 --> 32:56.285
Don't.

32:58.120 --> 33:00.168
I'm sorry.

33:04.640 --> 33:08.087
I just care about you too much
to be with you.

33:13.840 --> 33:15.444
Hey.

33:15.800 --> 33:17.802
Everything okay?

33:19.480 --> 33:21.369
Yeah. Just had a long day.

33:21.600 --> 33:24.763
- How's Roy?
- Well, he's alive. No thanks to me.

33:25.880 --> 33:28.247
You know, that was brave,
getting between us.

33:28.480 --> 33:30.403
- It took guts.
- Not really.

33:31.480 --> 33:35.121
I knew you wouldn't really hurt him.
You're not a killer.

33:37.080 --> 33:38.161
What's this for?

33:40.240 --> 33:41.287
Say goodbye.

33:41.480 --> 33:43.801
What? Wait, where are you going?

33:45.400 --> 33:46.606
To see an old friend.

34:01.240 --> 34:04.210
We've got every cop in this city
canvassing. We'll find this guy.

34:04.400 --> 34:06.402
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

34:06.640 --> 34:10.167
- You okay?
- Fine. Where were you?

34:10.800 --> 34:11.960
MOIRA:
He was with me.

34:17.120 --> 34:20.487
Odd to see the two of you
are getting along again.

34:21.280 --> 34:22.565
Thea.

34:43.080 --> 34:44.764
You knew about Roy.

34:48.199 --> 34:49.246
What?

34:49.480 --> 34:52.848
That's why you had your bodyguard
stalking me.

34:53.280 --> 34:55.931
Somehow, you knew
what was going on with him.

34:56.120 --> 34:57.451
[SCOFFS]

35:01.400 --> 35:03.209
I'm just trying to protect you.

35:04.200 --> 35:06.680
By not telling me the truth.

35:06.880 --> 35:08.564
Just like with Malcolm Merlyn.

35:10.040 --> 35:11.929
You know, the two of you...

35:12.120 --> 35:17.570
you think you're protecting me
by lying and by keeping secrets.

35:18.040 --> 35:20.202
But that's what's actually hurting me.

35:24.600 --> 35:26.250
You're absolutely right.

35:28.880 --> 35:32.248
- We need to turn a new page.
- It's not gonna be that simple.

35:32.480 --> 35:34.403
- Or easy.
MOIRA: I know.

35:34.720 --> 35:38.202
If the truth were easy for me,
we wouldn't be in this situation.

35:39.600 --> 35:42.444
But to start...

35:43.960 --> 35:48.170
there's something about Malcolm
that both you and Oliver need to know.

35:51.000 --> 35:52.047
Malcolm...

35:59.400 --> 36:01.243
Oliver.

36:01.960 --> 36:03.962
Oliver.

36:04.920 --> 36:06.410
SHADO:
I'm dead.

36:06.640 --> 36:08.608
[MOIRA CRYING]

36:13.200 --> 36:14.281
Oliver?

36:14.520 --> 36:15.965
Oliver.

36:19.440 --> 36:23.081
I was dead the last time
you were offered this choice.

36:23.320 --> 36:25.049
Slade.

36:25.640 --> 36:28.120
Oliver, what's happening?

36:28.320 --> 36:30.084
[THEA CRYING]

36:30.280 --> 36:32.647
I often wonder how you looked...

36:34.720 --> 36:37.405
when he pointed the gun at Shado...

36:37.760 --> 36:39.171
and took her from me.

36:39.360 --> 36:41.044
You psychopath.

36:41.240 --> 36:43.925
Shado. Shado wasn't yours.

36:44.120 --> 36:45.645
No, she was yours.

36:47.800 --> 36:49.802
Until you chose another woman over her.

36:50.000 --> 36:53.049
- That's not what happened!
- It is what happened.

36:53.240 --> 36:55.242
It is.

36:55.480 --> 36:56.891
She told me.

36:58.720 --> 37:01.041
What do you mean, she?
There's nobody there.

37:01.280 --> 37:03.169
Slade...

37:03.400 --> 37:06.927
you were on the island with Oliver.

37:09.120 --> 37:12.488
I thought I had known true despair...

37:12.680 --> 37:15.968
until I met your son.

37:17.360 --> 37:21.046
I trusted him to make the right choice.

37:21.240 --> 37:24.961
Let me make the right choice now. Kill me.

37:25.160 --> 37:26.241
MOIRA: No.
- No.

37:26.440 --> 37:27.771
Choose me, please.

37:27.960 --> 37:29.689
I am killing you, Oliver.

37:31.760 --> 37:35.128
- Only more slowly than you would like.
- Don't.

37:36.360 --> 37:39.409
- Choose.
- No, no. No.

37:39.600 --> 37:40.840
- Don't.
- Choose.

37:41.040 --> 37:43.486
OLIVER: Please.
SLADE: Choose.

37:44.680 --> 37:46.523
I swear to God, I am gonna kill you.

37:46.720 --> 37:48.484
- Choose.
- No. No.

37:49.440 --> 37:51.204
- No.
- No.

37:52.480 --> 37:54.050
Mom?

37:55.720 --> 38:00.601
- Mom, what are you doing?
- There's only one way this night can end.

38:00.840 --> 38:02.444
No.

38:07.560 --> 38:11.087
We both know that.

38:11.880 --> 38:14.451
Don't we, Mr. Wilson?

38:14.840 --> 38:16.524
OLIVER:
Mom, please don't.

38:16.720 --> 38:19.644
Both my children will live.

38:19.840 --> 38:22.969
Mom, what are you doing?

38:24.040 --> 38:25.530
Mom.

38:25.920 --> 38:27.081
Thea, I love you.

38:28.560 --> 38:30.927
- Close your eyes, baby.
- No!

38:32.000 --> 38:33.081
No.

38:34.200 --> 38:38.091
You possess true courage.

38:44.600 --> 38:46.648
I'm truly sorry.

38:51.240 --> 38:55.245
You did not pass that on to your son.

38:55.800 --> 38:56.961
THEA:
No!

38:57.640 --> 38:58.846
No.

39:09.120 --> 39:11.327
There is still one person...

39:12.280 --> 39:14.442
who has to die...

39:16.400 --> 39:18.482
before this can end.

39:18.680 --> 39:20.011
No.

39:25.120 --> 39:26.485
THEA:
Mom?

39:27.440 --> 39:28.930
Mom.

39:32.800 --> 39:34.928
Mom.

39:35.920 --> 39:38.605
Well, yeah, I'm sorry too.

39:40.040 --> 39:43.601
Well, listen, if there's ever anything
that I can do...

39:44.640 --> 39:46.404
Hello?

39:52.120 --> 39:54.248
Who was that?

39:54.440 --> 39:56.010
That was, um...

40:00.880 --> 40:02.928
She lost the baby.

40:05.120 --> 40:07.487
She said she's sad about it.

40:07.680 --> 40:10.923
And she's gonna go back to school
in Central City.

40:12.320 --> 40:13.970
Apparently, she has family there.

40:14.840 --> 40:17.889
I'm sure this has been
very traumatic for her.

40:18.080 --> 40:20.811
But it sounds for the best.

40:21.760 --> 40:24.127
- Sure.
- You okay?

40:25.160 --> 40:27.208
Yeah. Yes.

40:29.280 --> 40:34.241
I continue to be
the luckiest guy on the planet.

40:36.280 --> 40:39.284
What would I have done if she...?

40:47.880 --> 40:49.928
I'm just... I'm not ready to be a dad.

40:50.120 --> 40:51.167
No.

40:51.360 --> 40:53.442
But someday.

40:54.280 --> 40:56.123
It's my fondest hope for you.

40:59.880 --> 41:02.167
I'm glad I told you.

41:03.600 --> 41:06.206
I don't think I could've gotten
through this without you.

41:06.640 --> 41:09.610
You're never without me.

41:11.920 --> 41:14.890
My beautiful boy.

41:25.920 --> 41:28.002
So...

41:28.920 --> 41:30.410
I love you.

41:31.080 --> 41:32.844
I love you.

42:17.320 --> 42:19.322
[English - US - SDH]
